  "prompt": "What are some words that are the opposite of include?",
  "response": "Some words that are the opposite of \"include\" are:\n\n1. **Exclude** - To leave out or prevent from being part of something.  \n2. **Omit** - To leave out or fail to include.  \n3. **Remove** - To take away or eliminate.  \n4. **Eliminate** - To completely remove or get rid of.  \n5. **Reject** - To refuse to accept or consider.  \n6. **Ignore** - To deliberately not include or pay attention to.  \n7. **Bar** - To prevent or prohibit from being included.  \n8. **Blacklist** - To exclude from a list or group.  \n9. **Disregard** - To ignore or leave out intentionally.  \n10. **Preclude** - To prevent something from being included or happening.  \n\nThese words convey the idea of leaving something out or not including it in a particular context.",
